.TH VALKEY-SENTINEL 1 "2024"
.SH NAME
valkey-sentinel \- High availability monitoring for Valkey
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B valkey-sentinel
.RI configfile
.SH DESCRIPTION
Valkey Sentinel provides high availability for Valkey. It monitors Valkey
server instances, notifies administrators about changed state, and performs
automatic failover if a primary is not working as expected.
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.IP "configfile"
Read options from the specified Sentinel configuration file.
The default configuration file is
.B /etc/valkey/sentinel.conf
.SH NOTES
On Debian/Ubuntu systems,
.B valkey-sentinel
is managed via systemd. To start, stop or check status use:
.PP
.nf
    systemctl start valkey-sentinel.service
    systemctl stop  valkey-sentinel.service
    systemctl status valkey-sentinel.service
.fi
.PP
Multi-instance Sentinel is supported via the template unit:
.PP
.nf
    systemctl start valkey-sentinel@NAME.service
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR valkey-server (1),
.BR valkey-cli (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Valkey was written by the Valkey contributors <https://valkey.io>.
.PP
This manual page was written for the Debian/Ubuntu packages.
